von Freiheit und Verantwortung.  aThe discussions around the existence of human free will that have been carried out in recent years between philosophy, cognitive neuroscience, psychology and jurisprudence almost always boiled down to the bipolar answers of »yes« or »no« . Dirk Stederoth confronts this dualism with a sophisticated philosophical model of varying degrees of freedom, which at the same time takes the findings of the individual disciplines into consideration. Through this process, the gradual unfolding of the three dimensions »cognitive level« , »phases of action« and »developmental psychological levels« enables new and surprising perspectives on the central problems of freedom and responsibility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFree will and determinism. 4aEthik. 4aHandlungsphilosophie. 4aKognitionswissenschaft. 4aKulturphilosophie. 4aNeurowissenschaft. 4aPhilosophie des Geistes. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPhilosophische Anthropologie. 4aPsychologie. 4aRechtswissenschaft. 4aSozialität. 4aSozialphilosophie. 4aVerantwortung. 4aWillensfreiheit. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aCognitive Science.  aEthics.  aFree Will.  aJurisprudence.  aNeuroscience.  aPhilosophical Anthropology.  aPhilosophy of Action.  aPhilosophy of Culture.  aPhilosophy of Mind.  aPhilosophy.  aPsychology.  aResponsibility.  aSocial Philosophy.  aSocial Relations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2015z9783110438680oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-2